'''Moteb Saad Al-Harbi''' ({{langx|ar|متعب سعد الحربي}}; born 20 February 2000) is a Saudi Arabian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|left back]] for the [[Saudi Arabia national football team|Saudi Arabia national team]] and for [[Al Hilal SFC|Al-Hilal]].<ref>{{cite web |title=kooora |url=https://www.kooora.com/?player=125899}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=MOTEB AL-HARBI|url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/moteb-al-harbi/655299/}}</ref>

==Career==
Al-Harbi started his career at the youth team of [[Al-Shabab FC (Riyadh)|Al-Shabab]] and represented the club at every level. On 2 March 2020, he signed his first professional contract with [[Al-Shabab FC (Riyadh)|Al-Shabab]].<ref>{{cite web |title=الشباب يوقع عقداً احترافياً مع الحربي والمطيري|url=https://sa.hihi2.com/2020/03/02/p123537.html}}</ref> On 1 September 2024, Al-Harbi joined [[Al Hilal SFC|Al-Hilal]] on a five-year contract.<ref>{{cite web |title=رسميًا.. متعب الحربي هلالي لخمسة أعوام |url=https://sabq.org/sports/cu3ffb8t93}}</ref>

